Hmm,<p>The first part of your statement actually points towards "crazy overreach".<p>But you could interpret this action using all permutations of the imaginable adjectives and nouns:<p><pre><code>    {crazy, calculated} X {overreach, legal action} 
    >> 
    {"crazy overreach", "crazy legal action", 
     "calculated overreach", "calculated legal action"}
</code></pre>
And I'd be against all of them!
